
  <sn><md>### Central Tendency

**Central tendency** means `finding a single value` that represents the **center** or **typical value** of a dataset.

&gt; It tells you “what is the middle or most common value in the data?” <br>
&gt; It summarizes a whole set of numbers with one number.

In statistics, **mean**, **median**, and **mode** are the three most common measures of **central tendency**. They describe the center or typical value of a dataset. These measures help us summarize large sets of numbers into a single representative value.


:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Why we use central tendency :**  {.text-center}

* To understand the **overall pattern** of data
* To compare two groups
* To reduce big data into a simple summary
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
**Measures of central tendency** {.text-center}

1. **Mean** → average value
2. **Median** → middle value
3. **Mode** → most frequent value
:::
:::
